<h1>{{title}}</h1>
<p>seed={{seed}} step={{step}} size={{imgSize}} y={{seaLevel}} minY={{minY}} maxY={{maxY}}</p>
<p><b>NoiseRouter</b> = the final wired router used by worldgen (from <code>RandomState.router()</code>).</p>
<p><b>NoiseRouterData density functions</b> = the registered building blocks (splines, caches, noise sources) used to construct generator settings.</p>
<p><b>Note:</b> Overworld <code>depth</code> is derived from <code>overworld/offset</code> (plus a Y-gradient). <code>preliminary_surface_level</code> uses <code>overworld/offset</code> and <code>overworld/factor</code>, so similarity between them is expected.</p>
